greeting: Greetings from The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences! http://oeis.org/

results.name: Smallest base b such that there exist exactly n Wieferich pseudoprimes (composites c satisfying b^(c-1) == 1 (mod c^2)) less than b.
program: (PARI) for(n=1, 10, b=2; while(b > 0, i=0; forcomposite(c=2, b, if(Mod(b, c^2)^(c-1)==1, i++)); if(i==n, print1(b, ", "); break({1})); b++))
results.author: _Felix Fröhlich_, Mar 09 2015
